William B. Norman, Respondent v. Solomon Johnson, Appellant. Decided January 11, 1892. Appeal by defendant from judgment entered on verdict of jury and from order denying motion for a new trial. William B. Waring, attorney, and Charles W. Brooke of counsel, for appellant. Walter R. Beach, for respondent.

Before Freedman, P. J., and Gildersleeve, J.

Opinion by Gildersleeve, J.; Freedman P. J., concurred.

Judgment and order affirmed, with costs.
